            <entry xml:id="entry_igær" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>igær</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>печень</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>liver</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>de ‘gær fækalaj</orth></form>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">— в иронском употребительное выражение брани,
                        укора; но имеем ли здесь дело с ‘печеньюˈ или другим словом <ref type="xr"
                            target="#entry_ægær"/> ‘избытокˈ?</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">— in Iron, a widespread expression of abuse
                        or reproach; but does it include the word for ‘liverˈor rather a different
                        word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ægær"/> ‘surplusˈ?</note>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æxsyry cady īw x˳y ī, æmæ myn ūj igærtæ ærxæssūt, ændæra æz
                            amælʒynæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в молочном озере есть один кабан, достаньте мне его печень, а не то я
                                умру</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there is a boar in the milk lake, bring me its liver, or else I will
                                die</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>52</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>de ‘gær fækkalaj, Satana!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>чтобы рассыпалась твоя печень (?), Шатана!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>may your liver crumble (?), Satana!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            45</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Как и другие основные анатомические термины, является
                    общеиндоевропейским словом. Существовали два варианта основы: *%iyek''r-%i и
                    *%iyek''n-%i. Осетинская форма возводится к др.иран. *%iyakar-%i, и.е.
                    *%iyek''r-%i. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>jigar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>jerk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>jagar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>yēγən (← *yaxna)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>yina</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>gyagarrä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>yākar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>yakṛt</w></mentioned>, родительный падеж %iyaknah%i, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>jecur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ήπαρ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>jēknos</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/>
                        <w>aknas</w></mentioned> и пр. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"
                            /><biblScope>504</biblScope></bibl>). Начальный %ii%i в %iigær%i — из
                    %iуа%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_i"/> (артикль) из %iya%i, <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_izæd"/> д. из %iyazata%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 67, 90, III 160; Gr.
                            17</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is a Proto-Indo-European word, as well as other general
                    anatomical terms. Two stem variants existed: *%iyek''r-%i and *%iyek''n-%i. The
                    Ossetic form is traced to Old Iranian *%iyakar-%i, Indo-European *%iyek''r-%i.
                    Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>jigar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>jerk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>jagar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>yēγən (← *yaxna)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>yina</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>gyagarrä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>yākar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>yakṛt</w></mentioned>, genitive case %iyaknah%i, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>jecur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ήπαρ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>jēknos</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/>
                        <w>aknas</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"
                            /><biblScope>504</biblScope></bibl>). The initial %ii%i in %iigær%i —
                    from %iуа%i, like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_i"/> (the article) from %iya%i,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_izæd"/> Digor from %iyazata%i.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 67, 90, III 160;
                            Gr. 17</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
